
[1]scandalous

   SCAN'DALOUS, a.

   1. Giving offense.

   Nothing scandalous or offensive to any.

   2. Opprobrious; disgraceful to reputation; that brings shame or infamy;
   as a scandalous crime or vice. How perverted must be the mind that
   considers seduction or dueling less scandalous than larceny!

   3. Defamatory.
